# Git Rules

## Authorship

- Commits must be authored only as the repository owner.
- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any Cursor/agent co-author trailer.
- Never attribute commits, co-authorship, or contribution credit to Cursor, an agent, or any AI identity.
- Commit messages must contain only the intended subject/body — no agent metadata, trailers, or co-author lines.

## Commits

- Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
- Follow the repository’s existing commit message style.
- Do not push unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do not amend commits unless the user explicitly asks and amend conditions are met.
